adslAtucThreshold1DayEsL.name: adslAtucThreshold1DayEsL
adslAtucThreshold1DayEsL.description: The first time the value of the corresponding instance of adslAtucPerf1DayEsL reaches or exceeds this value within a given 1-day performance data collection period, an adslAtucEsLThreshTrap notification will be generated. The value '0' will disable the notification. The default value of this object is '0'.

adslLoopDiagIfIndex.name: adslLoopDiagIfIndex
adslLoopDiagIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the target interface to do loop diagnostic

adslLoopDiagProfileName.name: adslLoopDiagProfileName
adslLoopDiagProfileName.description: The profile used to do loop diagnostic

adslLoopDiagAction.name: adslLoopDiagAction
adslLoopDiagAction.description: Set to start to trigger ADSL2/ADSL2+ loop diagnostics. Once loop diagnostic is started, the status will reflect in adslLoopDiagCurrStatus. Set to cancel can allow user to cancel an ongoing loop diagnostics process. Reading this variable is meaningless, the result will always be 0.

adslLoopDiagLastStatus.name: adslLoopDiagLastStatus
adslLoopDiagLastStatus.description: This variable indicats status of last loop diagnostic on this line.

adslLoopDiagFailReason.name: adslLoopDiagFailReason
adslLoopDiagFailReason.description: Fail reason if loop diagnostic is failed. no fail reason is reported (0) IfIndex is not invalid (1) used profile does not exist or is inactive (2) line card does not exist (3) HWAPI return error (4) cancelled by user (5) line initialization fail (6) no atu-r is detected (7) line doesn't enter show-time state (8) timeout, result is not available (9) port monitoring is performing, loop diag can not perform at the same time (10)

adslLoopDiagResultAtucAttainableRate.name: adslLoopDiagResultAtucAttainableRate
adslLoopDiagResultAtucAttainableRate.description: Valid only while adslLoopDiagCurrStatus is success.

adslLoopDiagResultDsHlogM.name: adslLoopDiagResultDsHlogM
adslLoopDiagResultDsHlogM.description: This object provides an array of downstream Hlog(f) m. The m of subcarrier(i) is 256*Octect(2i)+Octect(2i+1), i=0~511. To get real value of Hlog(f), it is caculated as (6-m(i)/10). A special value 1023 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented.

adslLoopDiagResultUsHlogM.name: adslLoopDiagResultUsHlogM
adslLoopDiagResultUsHlogM.description: This object provides an array of upstream Hlog(f) m. The m of subcarrier(i) is 256*Octect(2i)+Octect(2i+1), i=0~63. To get real value of Hlog(f), it is caculated as (6-m(i)/10). A special value 1023 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented.

adslLoopDiagResultDsQuietLinePsdN.name: adslLoopDiagResultDsQuietLinePsdN
adslLoopDiagResultDsQuietLinePsdN.description: This object provides an array of downstream quiet line noise PSD n. The n of subcarrier(i) is Octect(i), i=0~511. To get real value of QLN(f), it is caculated as (-23-n(i)/2). A special value 255 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented.

adslLoopDiagResultUsQuietLinePsdN.name: adslLoopDiagResultUsQuietLinePsdN
adslLoopDiagResultUsQuietLinePsdN.description: This object provides an array of upstream quiet line noise PSD n. The n of subcarrier(i) is Octect(i), i=0~63. To get real value of QLN(f), it is caculated as (-23-n(i)/2). A special value 255 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented.

adslLoopDiagResultDsSnrN.description: This table used for ADSL2/ADSL2+ downstream loop diagnostics SNR.

adslLoopDiagResultUsSnrN.name: adslLoopDiagResultUsSnrN
adslLoopDiagResultUsSnrN.description: This table used for ADSL2/ADSL2+ upstream loop diagnostics SNR. value of subcarrier(i) is Octect(i)

askeyADSLConfProfileExtTable.name: askeyADSLConfProfileExtTable
askeyADSLConfProfileExtTable.description: This parameter represents the maximum nominal transmit PSD in the downstream direction during initialization and showtime (in dBm/Hz). It ranges from -60 to -40 dBm/Hz, with 0.1 dB steps.

adslAtucConfMaxNominalPSD.name: adslAtucConfMaxNominalPSD
adslAtucConfMaxNominalPSD.description: atu-c max nominal power spectrum desity

adslAturConfMaxNominalPSD.name: adslAturConfMaxNominalPSD

adslConfSRAModeEnabled.name: adslConfSRAModeEnabled
adslConfSRAModeEnabled.description: The seamless rate adaptive mode can force dynamic rate mode changing rate at runtime without retraining. This object is only applies to dynamic rate mode.

adslConfPwrMgtL2MinRate.name: adslConfPwrMgtL2MinRate
adslConfPwrMgtL2MinRate.description: minimum rate and low-bound to data rate for power management L2 state.

adslConfPwrMgtL2MaxRate.name: adslConfPwrMgtL2MaxRate
adslConfPwrMgtL2MaxRate.description: maximum rate to data rate for power management L2 state.

adslConfPwrMgtLowerL2ContinuousTime.name: adslConfPwrMgtLowerL2ContinuousTime
adslConfPwrMgtLowerL2ContinuousTime.description: The continuous time of line rate lower than L2 low-bound. Line can start transferring into L2 after this time pass.

adslConfPwrMgtL0Time.name: adslConfPwrMgtL0Time
adslConfPwrMgtL0Time.description: The minimum time in L0 state before line starts to check L2 criteria.

adslConfPwrMgtL3Accepted.name: adslConfPwrMgtL3Accepted
adslConfPwrMgtL3Accepted.description: This object indicates whether the ADSL lines accept CPE power management L3 request. If it is, the ADSL lines applied this profile will accept request from CPE and transfer their power management state into L3 by the CPE request.

adslConfAtucMinINP.name: adslConfAtucMinINP
adslConfAtucMinINP.description: ATUC(i.e. downstream) minimum INP(Impulse Noise Protect) capability. The object value indicates the multiple of INP symbol. For example, 'time-4' means four times.

adslConfAturMinINP.name: adslConfAturMinINP
adslConfAturMinINP.description: ATUR(i.e. upstream) minimum INP(Impulse Noise Protect) capability. The object value indicates the multiple of INP symbol. For example, 'time-4' means four times.
